The Letran Graduate School was founded in 1974 by Director Ramon C. Reyes. The Letran Graduate School began with the Master in Business Administration (MBA) program. In 1980, under the leadership of Dean Theodoro T. Abrigo, the Master in Business Administration Special Management Program (MBA SMP) was introduced. In 1995, Dean Perfecto Panuelos launched the Doctor of Business Administration (DBA) program.

The first Filipino rector and president of the Colegio de San Juan de Letran was Fr. Isidro Katigbak O.P., who served for four straight years. Letran has served by the majority of Spanish rectors and presidents for over 400 years.

In April 2007, Fr. Tamerlane Lana O.P. was elected rector and president of Letran, of the Intramuros and Abucay campuses, by the board of trustees to serve a four-year term until April 2011. Fr. Lana became the 80th rector of the Manila campus.

In June 2015, Fr. Clarence Victor C. Marquez, O.P. was elected 81st Rector and President of Letran Manila and Bataan.

In July 2023, Fr. Raymund Fernando P. Jose, O.P. was elected 82nd Rector and President of Letran Manila and Bataan.

Summary: 
According to the webpage, the college department began accepting female students in the 1970s. The Letran Graduate School was founded in 1974 with an MBA program, later adding an MBA Special Management Program in 1980 and a DBA program in 1995. Regarding the head of the school (rectors/presidents), Fr. Isidro Katigbak O.P. served as the first Filipino rector. In modern times, the 80th rector was Fr. Tamerlane Lana O.P. (elected April 2007), followed by the 81st rector Fr. Clarence Victor C. Marquez, O.P. (elected June 2015), and the 82nd rector Fr. Raymund Fernando P. Jose, O.P. (elected July 2023).
