The timeline of Saint Joseph's College of Quezon City is as follows: The institution was founded in 1932 under the leadership of directress Mother Magdala Verhuizen. The College department was subsequently opened in 1948. In the 1970s and 80s, the school offered a tuition-free evening high school. The Graduate School was established in 1979. In 2013, the High School department was merged with Kindergarten and Grade School to form the Basic Education Department, and later, the Senior High School Department was established in 2016. Current school leadership includes Sr. Esperanza Vistro as President, Sr. Julie Saguibo as Chairman, and Sr. Josephini P. Ambatali as VP for Academic Affairs. This provides a complete overview of the timeline and leadership requested.
